\paragraph{CCSequenceModel.}
The cooling loop (CC) controls a digital pump with discrete on/off behaviour and continuous speed, requiring a specialised output structure. The model shares the same encoder-decoder backbone as GRUController but replaces the single output head with two parallel heads: a binary classifier head producing a pump on/off logit, and a regression head predicting pump speed. Both heads are trained jointly, with binary cross-entropy loss on the classifier and mean squared error on the regressor.

\paragraph{Closed-loop composition.}
At inference, the five controller models predict their respective CV sequences independently. These generated CVs are injected into the plant model's target-window input, and the GRUPlant rolls out the full PV prediction horizon autoregressively. This mirrors the physical DCS structure in which controllers and plant are distinct functional blocks. The closed-loop dynamics are captured implicitly through training on historically observed DCS data; at inference, controllers and plant run independently with no runtime feedback between them.

\subsubsection{The Digital Twin as Simulator and Generator}

Our GRU digital twin serves two distinct roles:

\textbf{As a simulator:} The model learns the causal mapping from control
variables (CVs) to process variables (PVs). Given 300 seconds of valve
positions and pump speeds, it simulates what the physical plant should
produce — pressure, level, flow, and temperature. This is a forward
simulation of the boiler's response to control inputs.

\textbf{As a generator:} The model is conditioned on a scenario label
(0=normal, 1=AP\_no, 2=AP\_with, 3=AE\_no). For each scenario, it
generates realistic PV trajectories that match the statistical
distribution of that attack type. During inference with scenario=0,
it generates the expected normal behavior; the residual between
generated and actual PVs reveals attacks.

Thus, the same model functions as both a physics-informed simulator
(causal CV→PV mapping) and a conditional generator (scenario-conditioned
trajectory synthesis).

