\subsubsection{Tab 3 --- Loop Explorer (Diagnostics)}

The Loop Explorer provides per-loop diagnostics that profile each control loop along several physically meaningful axes: the SP, PV, and CV column names that anchor the loop in the dataset, the CV-to-PV response lag, the Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS) distributional fidelity statistic, and a derived pass/fail status. The tab opens with a Loop Reference table summarising the five loops side by side, followed by a horizontal bar chart visualising the KS statistic per loop against pass and fail thresholds. Figure~\ref{fig:loop_explorer} shows both elements together.

